.TH "iio_device_claim_direct_mode" 9 "iio_device_claim_direct_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iio_device_claim_direct_mode \- Keep device in direct mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iio_device_claim_direct_mode
.BI "(struct iio_dev *indio_dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "indio_dev" 12
the iio_dev associated with the device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the device is in direct mode it is guaranteed to stay
that way until \fBiio_device_release_direct_mode\fP is called.

Use with \fBiio_device_release_direct_mode\fP
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -EBUSY on failure
